<% @page_title = "Installing Node.js - #{deployment_walkthrough_page_title(locals)}" %>
<h1>Installing Node.js</h1>

<% if language_type == :meteor %>
<div class="note">
  Different versions of Meteor require different versions of Node.js. Please select your Meteor version to get the correct installation instructions for Node.js: <%= render_partial("/shared/meteor_picker_detailed.html") %>
</div>
<% end %>
Before you can deploy your app on the production server, you need to install Node.js. Here's how you can do that:

<table class="table table-bordered table-striped">
  <tr>
    <td>
      Debian, Ubuntu
    </td>
    <td>
      <p>Run the following commands to install Node.js from the <a href="https://nodesource.com/">NodeSource</a> APT repository. With these commands, we also install a compiler so that we are able to install native addons from npm.</p>
      <pre class="highlight<% if language_type == :meteor %> meteor v13<% end %>"><span class="prompt">$ </span>sudo apt-get update
<span class="prompt">$ </span>sudo apt-get install -y curl apt-transport-https ca-certificates &amp;&amp;
  curl --fail -ssL -o setup-nodejs https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_<% if language_type == :nodejs %>6.x<% end %><% if language_type == :meteor %>0.10<% end %> &amp;&amp;
  sudo bash setup-nodejs &amp;&amp;
  sudo apt-get install -y nodejs build-essential</pre>
<% if language_type == :meteor %>
      <pre class="highlight meteor v14"><span class="prompt">$ </span>sudo apt-get update
<span class="prompt">$ </span>sudo apt-get install -y curl apt-transport-https ca-certificates &amp;&amp;
  curl --fail -ssL -o setup-nodejs https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_4.x &amp;&amp;
  sudo bash setup-nodejs &amp;&amp;
  sudo apt-get install -y nodejs build-essential</pre>
<% end %>
<% if language_type == :meteor %>
      <pre class="highlight meteor v16"><span class="prompt">$ </span>sudo apt-get update
<span class="prompt">$ </span>sudo apt-get install -y curl apt-transport-https ca-certificates &amp;&amp;
  curl --fail -ssL -o setup-nodejs https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_8.x &amp;&amp;
  sudo bash setup-nodejs &amp;&amp;
  sudo apt-get install -y nodejs build-essential</pre>
<% end %>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>
      Red Hat, CentOS, Fedora
    </td>
    <td>
      <p>Run the following commands to enable <a href="https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/EPEL">EPEL</a> and to install Node.js from the <a href="https://nodesource.com/">NodeSource</a> YUM repository. With these commands, we also install a compiler so that we are able to install native addons from npm.</p>

      <pre class="highlight<% if language_type == :meteor %> meteor v13<% end %>"><span class="prompt">$ </span>sudo yum install -y epel-release curl
<span class="prompt">$ </span>curl --fail -sSL -o setup-nodejs https://rpm.nodesource.com/setup_<% if language_type == :nodejs %>6.x<% end %><% if language_type == :meteor %>0.10<% end %>
<span class="prompt">$ </span>sudo bash setup-nodejs
<span class="prompt">$ </span>sudo yum install -y nodejs gcc-c++ make</pre>
<% if language_type == :meteor %>
<pre class="highlight meteor v14"><span class="prompt">$ </span>sudo yum install -y epel-release curl
<span class="prompt">$ </span>curl --fail -sSL -o setup-nodejs https://rpm.nodesource.com/setup_4.x
<span class="prompt">$ </span>sudo bash setup-nodejs
<span class="prompt">$ </span>sudo yum install -y nodejs gcc-c++ make</pre>
<% end %>
<% if language_type == :meteor %>
<pre class="highlight meteor v16"><span class="prompt">$ </span>sudo yum install -y epel-release curl
<span class="prompt">$ </span>curl --fail -sSL -o setup-nodejs https://rpm.nodesource.com/setup_8.x
<span class="prompt">$ </span>sudo bash setup-nodejs
<span class="prompt">$ </span>sudo yum install -y nodejs gcc-c++ make</pre>
<% end %>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>
      Gentoo
    </td>
    <td>
      <% if language_type == :meteor %>Please install from source from <a href="http://www.nodejs.org/">www.nodejs.org</a> because the regular way (listed below) will probably install a newer version.<% end %>
      <pre class="highlight"><span class="prompt">$ </span>sudo emerge nodejs</pre>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>
      Arch Linux
    </td>
    <td>
      <% if language_type == :meteor %>Please install from source from <a href="http://www.nodejs.org/">www.nodejs.org</a> because the regular way (listed below) will probably install a newer version.<% end %>
      <pre class="highlight"><span class="prompt">$ </span>sudo pacman -S nodejs npm</pre>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>
      macOS
    </td>
    <td>
      Please download the Node.js macOS installer <% if language_type == :meteor %>(version <span class="meteor v13">0.10</span><span class="meteor v14">4</span><span class="meteor v16">8</span>.x)<% end %> from <a href="https://nodejs.org/download/">the Node.js download page</a> and run it.
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>
      Other Linux operating systems (32-bit or 64-bit only)
    </td>
    <td>
      Please download either the 32-bit or 64-bit Node.js Linux binaries <% if language_type == :meteor %>(version <span class="meteor v13">0.10</span><span class="meteor v14">4</span><span class="meteor v16">8</span>.x)<% end %> from <a href="https://nodejs.org/download/">the Node.js download page</a>.
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>
      Other operating systems
    </td>
    <td>
      Please install Node.js <% if language_type == :meteor %>(version <span class="meteor v13">0.10</span><span class="meteor v14">4</span><span class="meteor v16">8</span>.x)<% end %> from source from <a href="http://www.nodejs.org/">www.nodejs.org</a>.
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>

